	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Flickering looks great on an LCD screen, where screens tend to be slow to refresh, and it looks like the average of the two colors.  But on a CRT TV, where the screen can completely refresh at 60FPS without blur, flickering looks terrible.  If you have Batman, you can see this for yourself when you watch the intro.<br /><br />Also, you can post attachments here.  No need for mediafire.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


